Tools

     * [https://github.com/Gizra/generator-hedley]Yo Hedley! - Scaffold a
       headless Drupal backend, Angular app client, and Behat tests.

Modules

     * [https://www.drupal.org/project/restful]RESTful module - Allows
       Drupal to be operated via RESTful HTTP requests, using best
       practices for security, performance, and usability.
     * [https://www.drupal.org/project/og]Organic groups module - Enable
       users to create and manage their own 'groups'.
     * [https://www.drupal.org/project/message]Message - Enables logging
       and displaying system events in a number of different use cases.
     * [https://www.drupal.org/project/message_notify]Message Notify -
       Forward messages when they are generated.
     * [https://www.drupal.org/project/message_subscribe]Message Subscribe
       - Register to be notified when messages are generated for specific
       content.
     * [https://www.drupal.org/sandbox/bricel/2654176]Entities Diagram
       Graph - Generates a graph of the entities, fields and their
       relationship of a particular installation of Drupal 7.
     * [https://www.drupal.org/project/csv2sql]csv2sql - Convert CSV to
       SQL and create a table in your Drupal installation.
     * [https://www.drupal.org/project/logs_http]Logs HTTP - Provides JSON
       event pushing to Logs via the tag/http endpoint.
     * [https://www.drupal.org/project/features]Features - Enables the
       capture and management of features in Drupal. A feature is a
       collection of Drupal entities which taken together satisfy a
       certain use-case.
     * [https://www.drupal.org/project/commerce]Commerce - Used to build
       eCommerce websites and applications of all sizes.
     * [https://www.drupal.org/project/views]Views - Allows administrators
       and site designers to create, manage, and display lists of content.
     * [https://www.drupal.org/project/panels]Panels - Allows a site
       administrator to create customized layouts for multiple uses.
     * [https://www.drupal.org/project/ctools]Ctools - This suite is
       primarily a set of APIs and tools to improve the developer
       experience.
     * [https://www.drupal.org/project/search_api]Search API - Provides a
       framework for easily creating searches on any entity known to
       Drupal, using any kind of search engine.
     * [https://www.drupal.org/project/entity]Entity API - Extends the
       entity API of Drupal core in order to provide a unified way to deal
       with entities and their properties.
     * [https://www.drupal.org/project/entitycache]Entity cache - Puts
       core entities into Drupal's cache API.
     * [https://www.drupal.org/project/date]Date - Contains both a
       flexible date/time field type Date field and a Date API that other
       modules can use.
     * [https://www.drupal.org/project/devel]Devel - Suite of modules
       containing fun for module developers and themers.
     * [https://www.drupal.org/project/migrate]Migrate - Provides a
       flexible framework for migrating content into Drupal from other
       sources.
     * [https://www.drupal.org/project/entity_validator]Entity validator -
       Allows you to define a plugin and set methods to validate the
       object you'r dealing with.
     * [https://www.drupal.org/project/wysiwyg]WYSIWYG - Allows the use of
       client-side editors to edit content.

